<article class="form-partial">
  <h3>practice_form_5</h3>
  <p>Choose a form_for from any of the scenarios above and add HTML classes to it, add HTML IDs to it, pass in an option like creating a "blank" checkbox/radio/option so the user can choose to not have a given association at all.</p>

  <%= render 'shared/errors', object: post %>

  <%= form_for post do |f| %>
    <%= f.label :category_id %>
    <%= f.collection_select(:category_id, Category.dropdown, :id, :name) %>

    <%= f.label :title %>
    <%= f.text_field :title %><br>

    <%= f.label :body %>
    <%= f.text_area :body %><br>

    <%= f.label :tag_ids, "Select Tags" %>
    <%= f.collection_select(:tag_ids, Tag.all, :id, :name, {include_blank: "Select None"}, {multiple: true, class: 'combo-box'}) %>

    <%= f.submit %>
  <% end %> <!-- form_for post -->
</article>
